---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'What does Easel cost?',
    a: "Setting up and hosting an Easel site is completely free. A custom domain will run about $11 a year, if you don't already have one.",
  },
  {
    q: 'How can I trust Easel to be free forever?',
    a: "Once you've set up your instance, Easel has no control over your site. Even if we started charging a subscription fee tomorrow, we wouldn't be able to touch your site.",
  },
  {
    q: 'What accounts do I need?',
    a: "A free GitHub account is all you need: GitHub stores your site's files, and you can publish it straight to GitHub Pages from there. Prefer Netlify? You can connect a free Netlify account instead — Easel sets up whichever you choose.",
  },
  {
    q: 'What prior coding knowledge do I need?',
    a: "None! Easel uses a simple editor, and you'll never touch the code behind your site if you don't want to. If you have some experience, we support custom HTML, CSS, and JS for making tweaks you want.",
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I use a custom domain?',
    a: 'Absolutely! Custom domains are free on both GitHub Pages and Netlify.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What kind of work can I show?',
    a: "Anything visual! Easel is built around image galleries, so it's a great fit for illustrators, photographers, painters, designers, and more.",
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I change how my site looks?',
    a: "Yes! You can adjust colors, fonts, and layout right from the editor, no code required.",
  },
  {
    q: 'Who owns my site and content?',
    a: "You do, fully. Your site lives on your own GitHub account (and Netlify, if you chose it), so it stays online whether or not you keep using Easel.",
  },
  {
    q: 'I have an unanswered question or idea for a feature!',
    a: 'Shoot me an email at easel@rosematcha.com.',
  },
];
---

<section class="section faq" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>You should know&hellip;</h2>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {faqs.map((item) => (
        <details class="faq__item">
          <summary>{item.q}</summary>
          <p>{item.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq__list {
    margin-top: var(--space-5);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .faq__item {
    border: var(--border-bold);
    background: var(--c-white);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-hard-sm);
  }
  .faq__item summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .faq__item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq__item summary::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--c-blue);
  }
  .faq__item[open] summary::after { content: '\2013'; }
  .faq__item p {
    padding: 0 var(--space-4) var(--space-4);
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--c-stone);
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .faq__list { margin-top: var(--space-4); }
    /* Roomier tap targets for thumbs. */
    .faq__item summary {
      padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-3);
      font-size: 1.0625rem;
      gap: var(--space-3);
    }
    .faq__item p { padding: 0 var(--space-3) var(--space-4); }
  }
</style>
